    "glp1_faq": {
      "type": "bloomli-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "q1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why is my hair shedding more since I started losing weight?",
            "answer": "<p>Rapid weight loss can temporarily shift more hairs into their natural resting-and-shedding phase, and eating less can leave gaps in the nutrients hair depends on. For most women it is common and temporary, and nutrition is one part you can actively support.*</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will this stop my shedding?",
            "answer": "<p>No. Bloomli cannot stop shedding. What it can do is support your hair with nutrients it may be missing right now, and help it look fuller over time.* If shedding worries you, talk to your healthcare provider.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I take this with my medication?",
            "answer": "<p>Bloomli is a general daily nutritional supplement, not a drug. Because everyone's situation is different, talk to your healthcare provider about adding any supplement alongside your medication.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long until I see a difference?",
            "answer": "<p>Hair grows in cycles, so meaningful changes take time. Give a consistent routine at least a few months before judging how your hair looks and feels.* Individual experiences vary.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "q5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is it safe, and what's in it?",
            "answer": "<p>Key actives per two gummies include 6,000mcg biotin, marine collagen, PABA, silicon, zinc, iodine and vitamins A, C, D, E, B6, B12, folate and B5. Gluten-free. Contains fish (tilapia) and tree nuts (coconut); the facility processes common allergens. Made in the USA.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        },
        "q6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I cancel?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Subscriptions are flexible, so you can pause or cancel anytime, and shipping is free while you subscribe.</p>",
            "open_by_default": false
          }
        }
      },
